  "body": "I'd like to impersonate a contract during a mainnet fork test, but it has no fund and no payable receive function.\r\n\r\nIt seems as of today that there is no way for the contract to receive ETH and thus pay for the gas when impersonating.\r\n\r\nAm I correct? Would be a great feature, especially for testing governance systems that have proposal executors :)\r\n\r\n",
